<br>
blademasters are the “Light Tanks” Of Hibernia. We give up the heavier defense of Heroes, and the magic of Champions to be the high-damage-output tanks in the realms.<br>
<br>
Or are we?<br>
<br>
Issues:<br>
<br>
Consistently, across the board, blademasters are complaining about lack of damage versus Heroes, and versus our light tank counterparts in other realms. In one-on-one testing, a Mercenary does slightly more damage aganst us using Amethyst Slash, the typical Blade style for an Albion tank. Versus a Berzerker, there is no contest, they completely and totally outdamage us.<br>
<br>
In Hibernia, Large Weapons styles do about 75-100% more style samage than CD styles, and in Midgard, Left Axe Styles do even more damage. A Style like Doublefrost, for example, adds over +100 to style damage, versus the typical +30 for Hurricane, the most commany used CD Style.<br>
<br>
All of the blademasters defensive skills are percentage based. This is not so much an issue in PvE as it is in RvR. Throw into the mix the issue that namy stles have an increase % to hit a player, and this makes parrying a player rather difficult.<br>
<br>
A majority of our styles are reactionary or positional. These are good styles for PvE, but not very good for RvR. This is another reason why our style damage needs to be increased, we only have a few styles we can use in RvR because of issues like strafing penalties (notthat I’ve even been in a fight long enough to be able to attempt a positional on a PC char.)<br>
<br>
Triple Wield has an issue of canceling out enchanter damage adds when active, and most agree that the timer on it could be lowered somewhat without this becoming overpowering. <br>
<br>
There is a growing segment of the blademaster population that is speccing in Blunt or Piercing weapons. There are issues with this, as there are not many off-hand wieldable blunt or piercing weapons, as well as there not being many good drops. There has been some recent inprovement with this, but adding + ro spec type as well as +CD on these drops would be a freat benefit to those who use them.<br>
<br>
<br>
Proposed solutions:<br>
<br>
Please add bonus damage to both swings when using Celtic Dual styles. This one thing, above all others, would solve many of the complaints that characters have about their class.<br>
<br>
At the time of this report writing, the CD styles are being looked at. <br>
<br>
Turning down the timer on Triple Wield, and making it stack with other damage adds would be a “good” thing.<br>
<br>
In closing:<br>
<br>
blademasters are one of the least played classes in the game, and the least played melee character. Other melee can do everything we can, with better damage, more defense. What real reason is there to play a blademaster?<br>
<br>
&quot;(I) Can't even log on my BM anymore without wanting to log off in 10mins. =p Only thing that keeps me around are my friends.”<br>
<br>
--DK--<br>
